Brisbane Airport Said to Be Close to Signing A$500 Million Loan

-- B y   S a r a h   M c D o n a l d
-- 
2011-09-21T02:10:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/brisbane-airport-said-to-be-close-to-signing-a-500-million-loan.html
Brisbane Airport Corp. is close to
signing a A$500 million ($513 million) loan facility with four
banks to refinance existing debt, according to a person familiar
with the matter.  National Australia Bank Ltd. (NAB) ,  Commonwealth Bank of
Australia (CBA) , Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi UFJ Ltd. and Mizuho
Corporate Bank Ltd. are providing the four-year revolving loans,
the person said, asking not to be named as the details are
private. The facility is structured as a bilateral agreement
with each lender and is likely to be signed by early October,
the person said.  Brisbane Airport Chief Financial Officer Tim Rothwell
declined to comment on the financing plans when contacted by
phone by Bloomberg News today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sarah McDonald in Sydney at 
 smcdonald23@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shelley Smith at 
 ssmith118@bloomberg.net  